{
  "Johto Region": {
    "type": "Region",
    "description": "Johto is a storied expanse of pastoral valleys, silver-capped peaks, and old-world cities where the line between history and the present is lovingly blurred. Settled west of Kanto and unified by a reverence for tradition, Johto offers a slower-paced backdrop for bonds to deepen, legends to whisper, and relationships—romantic, spiritual, and personal—to find unguarded space to blossom. It is a region of memory, restraint, and quiet resilience.",

    "geography": {
      "position": "Western Tairiku, across the Kanjoh Range from Kanto",
      "climate": "Misty forests, lake-ringed mountains, and seasonal valleys. Springs are brief and full of blossoms. Winters are long and contemplative.",
      "landmark_elements": [
